1 Section 1. Section 75-307, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 75-307 (1) Certificated intrastate motor carriers, including common
4 and contract carriers, any motor carrier transporting household goods
5 under a license issued pursuant to section 75-304.03, and any motor
6 carrier transporting employees of a railroad carrier under a license
7 issued pursuant to section 75-304.04 shall comply with reasonable rules
8 and regulations prescribed by the commission governing the filing with
9 the commission, the approval of the filings, and the maintenance of proof
10 at such carrier's principal place of business of surety bonds, policies
11 of insurance, qualifications as a self-insurer, or other securities or
12 agreements, in such reasonable amount as required by the commission,
13 conditioned to pay, within the amount of such surety bonds, policies of
14 insurance, qualifications as a self-insurer, or other securities or
15 agreements, any final judgment recovered against such motor carrier for
16 bodily injuries to or the death of any person resulting from the
17 negligent operation, maintenance, or use of motor vehicles under such
18 certificate, permit, or license or for loss or damage to property of
19 others. No certificate or permit shall be issued to a common or contract
20 carrier, no license shall be issued to a motor carrier transporting
21 household goods under section 75-304.03 or employees of a railroad
22 carrier under section 75-304.04, nor shall such certificate, permit, or
23 license remain in force unless such carrier complies with this section
24 and the rules and regulations prescribed by the commission pursuant to
25 this section.
26 (2) The commission may, in its discretion and under its rules and
27 regulations, require any certificated carrier, any motor carrier
28 transporting household goods under a license issued pursuant to section
29 75-304.03, and any motor carrier transporting employees of a railroad
30 carrier under a license issued pursuant to section 75-304.04 to file a
31 surety bond, policies of insurance, qualifications as a self-insurer, or
