1 other securities or agreements, in a sum to be determined by the
2 commission, to be conditioned upon such carrier making compensation to
3 shippers or consignees for all property belonging to shippers or
4 consignees and coming into the possession of such carrier in connection
5 with its transportation service. Any carrier which may be required by law
6 to compensate a shipper or consignee for any loss, damage, or default for
7 which a connecting motor common carrier is legally responsible shall be
8 subrogated to the rights of such shipper or consignee under any such
9 bond, policies of insurance, or other securities or agreements to the
10 extent of the sum so paid.
11 (3) When setting the rates for required policies of insurance
12 pursuant to this section, the commission shall require at least a minimum
13 of one million dollars in uninsured and underinsured insurance coverage
14 per occupant.
15 (4) (3) In carrying out this section, the commission may classify
16 motor carriers and regulated motor carriers taking into consideration the
17 hazards of the operations of such carriers and the value of the household
18 goods carried. Nothing contained in this section shall be construed to
19 authorize the commission to compel motor carriers other than those
20 transporting household goods under section 75-309 or under a license
21 issued pursuant to section 75-304.03 to carry cargo insurance.
22 (5) (4) This section does not apply to transportation network
23 companies.
24 Sec. 2. Original section 75-307, Revised Statutes Cumulative
25 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
